text: most citizens of el salvadore don't have the luxury of "investing" in an asset class like bitcoin. it is being used a medium for trade/exchange.

The citizens of El Salvador are not using BTC as a store of value or as an investment/asset class. They are using digital currency as medium for exchange. Thus they are not "waiting out" for $100k in bitcoin. They are buying groceries, paying bills, etc.
You and other investors in btc can afford to lose ten percent in day. That is not the case of those in El Salvador. And I wasnt being snarky.
Congratulations to all those citizens in El Salvador that have put their money into bitcoin over the weekend - and have lost -10% of the value of their BTC holdings.

One thing I am certain of... the country of El Salvador, which is now buying bitcoin, is not typically an early adopter. @thedomino @SquawkCNBC @JohnFMauldin @pboockvar @andrewrsorkin @carlquintanilla @tomkeene @ferrotv
